Spanish defender Pique played the full 90 minutes as Barcelona beat Rayo Vallecano 2-0 in La Liga

Pique has struggled for form this season but played the full 90 minutes as Luis Enrique's side beat Rayo Vallecano at the Nou Camp.

Lionel Messi scored mid-way through the first half and Neymar added a second just 60 seconds later, it was a blow from which the hosts, who finished the game with nine men, would not recover.

Barcelona are unbeaten in La Liga, and remain two points clear at the top of the table while rivals Real Madrid are up to fourth after they crushed Athletic Bilbao 5-0 at the Bernabeu.  

